%N A393662 A sequence arising from the 3-Bratteli diagram, a(n) = 3^(n - 3)*(16*n - 15), n>=3.
%C A393662 a(n) denotes the total number of descents of all paths starting from a vertex on the 2(n+1)-th floor in the 3-Bratteli diagram and ending at all vertices on the first floor.
%H A393662 Tamilselvi Annamalai, <a href="/A393662/b393662.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A393662 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bratteli_diagram">Bratteli diagram</a>.
%H A393662 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (6,-9).
%F A393662 a(n) = 3^(n - 3)*(16*n - 15), n>=3.
%F A393662 G.f: x^3*(33-51*x)/(1-3*x)^2.
%F A393662 E.g.f.: (10 - 2*x - 51*x^2 + 2*exp(3*x)*(16*x - 5))/18. - _Stefano Spezia_, Feb 25 2026
%p A393662 a(n):= 3^(n - 3)*(16*n - 15);
%p A393662 num_list := [seq(eval(a(n), n = i), i = 3 .. 100)];
%t A393662 LinearRecurrence[{6, -9}, {33, 147}, 26] (* _Hugo Pfoertner_, Feb 24 2026 *)
